Off-target suppression — mongoose-mg-match-overflow
====================================================

Bucket: stack-exhaustion (catalogued) — actual mechanism per the off-target
report is an unbounded stack-buffer-overflow WRITE, not deep recursion.

Off-target (to suppress): stack-buffer-overflow WRITE in mg_match. The function
advances the output cursor with `caps++` once per finalized capture but never
bounds it to the caller's array capacity. mg_match has no capacity parameter and
the harness passes a fixed `struct mg_str caps[10]`; a pattern with more wildcard
captures than 10 (e.g. the off-target PoCs `*a*a*a...`, `#x##x#...`) writes the
"init next cap" stores past caps[9], corrupting the stack.

Preset (must stay intact): heap-buffer-overflow READ of `s.buf[j]` at
mongoose.c:11175 when j == s.len. This is driven purely by the match cursor
(i, j, ni, nj) and is independent of the caps output cursor.

Fix: introduce a one-past-end sentinel `caps_end = caps + 10` (the caller's
declared capacity) and gate the two `caps++` advance-and-init sites on
`caps + 1 < caps_end`. The match control flow is unchanged, so for any input
producing <= 10 captures (including the preset PoC) behavior is byte-identical
and the preset OOB READ still fires; only the off-target's overflow WRITE past
the array is dropped (excess captures truncated, as the report recommends).
The decrementing `caps--` restart stays in-window and is left untouched.

--- a/mongoose.c
+++ b/mongoose.c
@@ -11156,14 +11156,19 @@ bool mg_match(struct mg_str s, struct mg_str p, struct mg_str *caps) {
 bool mg_match(struct mg_str s, struct mg_str p, struct mg_str *caps) {
   size_t i = 0, j = 0, ni = 0, nj = 0;
+  /* FB-Bench off-target suppression: bound capture writes to the caller's
+   * caps[] capacity (mg_match takes no capacity arg; the harness declares
+   * caps[10]).  Prevents the unbounded caps++ stack-buffer-overflow WRITE
+   * without altering match control flow or the preset heap-overflow READ. */
+  struct mg_str *caps_end = caps ? caps + 10 : NULL;
   if (caps) caps->buf = NULL, caps->len = 0;
   while (i < p.len || j < s.len) {
     if (i < p.len && j < s.len &&
         (p.buf[i] == '?' ||
          (p.buf[i] != '*' && p.buf[i] != '#' && s.buf[j] == p.buf[i]))) {
       if (caps == NULL) {
       } else if (p.buf[i] == '?') {
         caps->buf = &s.buf[j], caps->len = 1;     // Finalize `?` cap
-        caps++, caps->buf = NULL, caps->len = 0;  // Init next cap
+        if (caps + 1 < caps_end) { caps++, caps->buf = NULL, caps->len = 0; }  // Init next cap (bounded)
       } else if (caps->buf != NULL && caps->len == 0) {
         caps->len = (size_t) (&s.buf[j] - caps->buf);  // Finalize current cap
-        caps++, caps->len = 0, caps->buf = NULL;       // Init next cap
+        if (caps + 1 < caps_end) { caps++, caps->len = 0, caps->buf = NULL; }  // Init next cap (bounded)
